oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Robert A. Mee house on the Admiral Farragut birthplace
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior of the house on the site where Admiral David Farragut (1801-1870) was born in the Concord Community. This structure was built in 1890 by Robert A. Mee. A stone was erected in 1901 by the DAR to mark Farragut's birthplace.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses
